{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"5e37a965-3dc6-44b4-b120-a8d35cc61393","content":"On macOS, if `createdump` isn't bundled with your NativeAOT app, you can still get a crash dump:\n\n1. **Enable core dumps** in the shell:\n   ```bash\n   ulimit -c unlimited\n   ```\n\n2. **Check for Apple crash reports** — macOS automatically writes `.ips` / `.crash` files to:\n   ```\n   ~/Library/Logs/DiagnosticReports/\n   /Library/Logs/DiagnosticReports/\n   ```\n\n3. **Use `lldb`** to attach or open a core file:\n   ```bash\n   lldb --core /cores/core.<pid> /path/to/your/app\n   ```\n   macOS writes cores to `/cores/` (the directory must exist and be writable).\n\n4. **If `/cores/` doesn't work**, check that SIP (System Integrity Protection) isn't blocking core dumps and that the `/cores` directory has appropriate permissions:\n   ```bash\n   sudo mkdir -p /cores\n   sudo chmod 1777 /cores\n   ```\n\n5. **Alternatively**, use `dotnet-dump collect` (if the process is still alive) or configure the `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType` and `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName` environment variables before launch to request a managed dump on crash — though these rely on the crash-dump infrastructure being present in the runtime.\n\nFor NativeAOT specifically, `lldb` with the core file is typically the most reliable fallback since the app runs as a fully native binary.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d02d874a-a436-497d-a48d-9c775587aafe","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about recovering crash dumps on macOS for NativeAOT apps when `createdump` isn't available. This seems like a general knowledge question about .NET NativeAOT debugging on macOS. Let me answer from my knowledge — no need to search the codebase unless there's relevant documentation in the repo.\n\nActually, let me check if there's any relevant documentation in the repository first, since this is a .NET-related repo with plugins.","outputTokens":481},"id":"cc4b8759-982e-465d-8890-1fe3132568ec","timestamp":"2026-04-08T01:03:37.891Z","parentId":"d9b59347-9a00-48bb-a803-adae97136ea9"}
